		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">SK tactics<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Nov 7th 2:41 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=9736261194636&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=9736261194636&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=9736261194636"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9736261194636></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I was wondering if any of my dark brothers knew any general class strategies.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am specifically interested in tactics that allow you to take tough yellow or (EEK) red mobs.  Where to go, how to fight, and what spells to use are also of interest.<br><br>Ndarain Darkheart<br>22 Speedy DE SK - Xegony&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Nov 12th 10:01 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=9736261194636&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=9740845099541"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9740845099541></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=2307"><span id=>Nazragul</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>11 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Nazragul&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, the best soloing tactic Ive ever employed is fear-kiting and it has allowed me to take down yellow opponents on numerous occasions. Fear kiting consists of casting darkness on a distant enemy to slow them down and casting fear on them before they get into melee range with you. You then chase them, you and your trusty pet beating at their back as they flee. Recast fear as it wears off and darkness as well. Dont be surprised if you get resisted quite a bit against enemies even strength with you or higher, so a lot of times fear-kiting can turn into a war of attrition as you just melee the last third of the critter's hps. If you want insurance, send in your pet before you cast dark, to make sure you get it in. This can result in the premature loss of your pet, however, and you will miss the extra attacks as you chase it. Also because of the resistance factor, I dont usually try to solo yellows unless there are guards within striking distance or I have HT up. Im sure you can find better written and more detailed documents on fear-kiting elsewhere, but those are the basics.<br><br>As far as where to practice soloing at level 22, all I can say is The Overthere. You can get a bind at the docks and go hunt animals ranging from about 16-23 if I remember correctly. They do not cast, do not assist each other, and drop plats and items worth plats. (dont sell in overthere though, those damned gnome machines are rip-offs) Look out for rhinos though...they are extremely fast and thus are a little underconned for fear-kiters.<br><br>Finally, as far as soloing red monsters...I have never really tried it. It is very difficult to get darkness and fear to stick on them, and your pet will get sliced and diced if left to tank.<br><br>Good luck to you in your soloing career, hope this advice from a humble 30th season knight can help you.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Nazragul Xarn, 40th Season Knight of the Dismal Rage<br>Morell-Thule</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
